description:
Create internal HTTP helper for making authenticated API requests.

## Requirements
Implement the internal `do` method on Client:

```go
func (c *Client) do(ctx context.Context, method, path string, body, result any) error {
    // 1. Build request
    // 2. Set Auth header: Authorization: Token <id>:<secret>
    // 3. Execute request
    // 4. Check response status
    // 5. On error: return APIError
    // 6. On success: unmarshal JSON into result
}
```

## Technical Details
- Support GET, POST, PUT, DELETE methods
- JSON content type for request/response
- Context support for cancellation
- Proper URL joining (BaseURL + path)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] do() method implemented
- [ ] Auth header correctly formatted
- [ ] JSON marshaling/unmarshaling works
- [ ] Context cancellation supported
- [ ] Unit tests with httptest.Server

Ensure all exported types and functions have proper GoDoc comments.

## Requirements
From PRD Section 8 (Definition of Done):
- Alle public APIs dokumentiert (GoDoc)

## Documentation Standards
- Package-level doc comment in bookstack.go
- All exported types documented
- All exported functions documented
- All exported constants/variables documented
- Include usage examples in doc comments where helpful

## Example
```go
// Client is the Bookstack API client. Use NewClient to create a new instance.
// Client is safe for concurrent use.
type Client struct {
    // Books provides access to the Books API.
    Books *BooksService
    ...
}

// NewClient creates a new Bookstack API client with the provided configuration.
// BaseURL, TokenID, and TokenSecret are required.
//
// Example:
//
//    client := bookstack.NewClient(bookstack.Config{
//        BaseURL:     "https://docs.example.com",
//        TokenID:     "token-id",
//        TokenSecret: "token-secret",
//    })
func NewClient(cfg Config) *Client
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Package documentation present
- [ ] All exported types documented
- [ ] All exported functions documented
- [ ] Documentation renders correctly in pkg.go.dev style
- [ ] No golint documentation warnings
